data.chText: 里面的；向内的；内部的；接近中心的
data.enText: inside; towards or close to the centre of a place

data.chText: 内心的；未表达出来的；隐藏的
data.enText: private and secret; not expressed or shown to other people

data.chText: 她不大流露她的内心自我。
data.enText: She doesn't reveal much of her inner self.

word_means: 射中接近靶心部分的一发

means: 射中接近靶心部分的一发

ex.chText: 很难了解他内心的想法。
ex.enText: It is difficult to know his inner thoughts.

synonyms.bx: 指位于某物内部或靠近其中心位置的，也可指想法、情感等藏于内心之中而未表达出来的，只作定语。

d: 内部的，靠近中心的；内心的

ex.chText: 报纸的内页已经被撕了。
ex.enText: The inside pages of the newspaper have been torn out.

ex.chText: 你外套的内兜里有什么东西？
ex.enText: What is in the inside pocket of your coat?

synonyms.bx: 指在某物内部的，只作定语。

ex.chText: 一些科学家一直在研究人造内脏。
ex.enText: Some scientists have been doing research on artificial internal organs.

ex.chText: 只有该公司的职员才能阅读内部邮件。
ex.enText: Only employees of the company can read the internal mail.

synonyms.bx: 指位于身体、公司、组织、国家等内部的，也可指内心的，通常作定语。

ex.enText: There is an inward flow of positive charges.

synonyms.bx: 指想法、情感等存于内心而未向他人吐露的，作此义解时只作定语；也可指方向朝内或朝向中心的。

tr: inside or closer to the inside of the body

example: Beethoven's manuscript looks like a bloody record of a tremendous inner battle"- Leonard Bernstei
she thinks she has no soul, no interior life, but the truth is that she has no access to it"- David Denb
an internal sense of rightousness"- A.R.Gurney,Jr
the internal contradictions of the theory

value.def: The inner parts of something are the parts which are contained or are enclosed inside the other parts, and which are closest to the centre.

example.ex: She got up and went into an inner office...
example.tran: 她起身进了里间办公室。

example.ex: Wade stepped inside and closed the inner door behind him.
example.tran: 韦德走进去，随手带上了里面的门。

value.def: Your inner feelings are feelings which you have but do not show to other people.

example.ex: Loving relationships will give a child an inner sense of security...
example.tran: 亲昵关系会给予孩子内心一种安全感。

example.ex: Michael needed to express his inner tensions.
example.tran: 迈克尔需要宣泄一下他内心的紧张。

trans: 内心世界；内在世界；内部世界；精神世界；里世界
内耳，内耳迷路(包括听觉器官和平衡器官)
内衬；橡胶密封层；气密层
内在美；内在美容；内涵；内在的美；内美
